[32m│[0m ## Character Filter Analysis                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Blocked Characters/Strings:**                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **Backticks (`)** - All tests containing backticks returned: "Sorry you   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m can't use: '`'"                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **Parentheses `(` and `)`** - Tests 4 and 5 returned: "Sorry you can't    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m use: '('"                                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. **The word "javascript"** - Test 6 returned: "Sorry you can't use:        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 'javascript'"                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. **Single quotes (')** - Appear to be allowed in some contexts but trigger [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m filters when combined with certain payloads                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Reflection Context:**                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```html                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m <input type=text name=name placeholder="Enter your name..." ><img src="">    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The payload is reflected in the `src` attribute of an img tag, making it     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m suitable for javascript: protocol exploitation, but the filter blocks direct [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m use of "javascript:".                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ## Findings Summary                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Test Results:                                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **`' onerror=alert`XSS``** - ❌ Blocked (backtick)                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **`" onerror=alert`XSS``** - ❌ Blocked (backtick)                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. **`javascript:alert`XSS``** - ❌ Blocked (backtick)                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. **`javascript:eval('alert\x28\x27XSS\x27\x29')`** - ❌ Blocked            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m (parentheses)                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 5. **`javascript:String.fromCharCode(97,108,...)`** - ❌ Blocked             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m (parentheses)                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 6. **`javascript:alert&#40;'XSS'&#41;`** - ❌ Blocked (javascript keyword)   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **HTML Entity Bypass Attempt Failed:** The filter checks the raw input       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m string before HTML entity decoding, so `&#40;` and `&#41;` don't bypass the  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m parentheses restriction.                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ## Filter Bypass Strategy Needed                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m To execute `alert('XSS')` without:                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Parentheses `()`                                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Backticks ``                                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - The word "javascript"                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Potential approaches to explore:**                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **Alternative protocols** - Use `data:text/html;base64,...` or            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `vbscript:` (if allowed)                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **Unicode encoding** - Try URL-encoded variants that decode differently   [32m│[0m
